        </h1>
        <h2>
			<p>U.S. campaigns for regime change characteristically focus on the “madness” of the “dictators” to be toppled. In the case of North Korea, the narrative is spiced by the country’s developing nuclear capabilities &#8212; which North Korea views as its main line of defense against . . . regime change.</p>
